         <div type="translation">
            <p>i. a: [ . . .] because of? [ . . .?Aphrodi]sians [ . . .] curat[?or . . . ] name [ . . .] decree [ . . .]</p>
            <p>i. b: ...] with the care that befits you. At the same time taking thought too for the collection of the moneys that are owing to the city, I have also sent you instructions from us ?in order that you may have our advice in the matters to be managed. Farewell.</p>
            <p>ii. Place of Kyriakos, trouser-maker.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>i. See <bibl n="jmr1982">Reynolds,<title> Aphrodisias and Rome</title>, 178</bibl>. a does not add very much, but confirms the suggestion that a curator <term xml:lang="grc-Latn">rei publicae</term> was involved.</p>
            <p>ii: See discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="XI.5" target=".xml"/> and  <ref type="eAla-text" n="XI.9" target=".xml"/> .</p>
         </div>
